    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="231"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.20219/55</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Price</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 390</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 21, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 1388 of May
                    15, 1917, confidential, enclosing a copy of a note from the Panaman Foreign
                    Office forwarding a complaint of the Consul of Sweden, accredited to Panama,
                    concerning the internment of <persName>Oscar W. Eliassen</persName> with the
                    Germans at Taboga Island.<note n="1" xml:id="d231fn1">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>In reply I have to say that you are authorized to advise the Panaman Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs that this Government will hold <pb facs="0318" n="234"
                        xml:id="pg_234"/> Panama harmless against loss on account of having
                    heretofore interned persons in conformity with this Government’s desire,
                    provided this Government shall be kept informed of the proceedings of claimants
                    and be satisfied that the Government of Panama resisted their claims in good
                    faith.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
